"{\"uid\": \"skynews.com.au-australia-news-sport-united-states-sprint-star-noah-lyles-seizes-olympic-gold-in-photo-finish-100m-sprint-at-paris-2024-news-story-d1c26b18d772a335f240e02f14551252\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"In a breathtaking photo finish, US megastar Noah Lyles has cemented his place as the fastest man in the world after winning the 100m sprint at the 2024 Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 167, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 32, \"end\": 34, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.5780112612882662, \"rank\": 0.73003160169031, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 44, \"end\": 54, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris 2024 Olympic Games has crowned a new fastest man in the world as United States sprint star Noah Lyles clinched gold in the 100m sprint on Sunday.\", \"from\": 169, \"to\": 324, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 244, \"end\": 257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.8198445947774843, \"rank\": 0.2162886365285577, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 270, \"end\": 280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The US sprinter penned his name alongside former gold medallists Usain Bolt, Carl Lewis and Jesse Owens as he scraped past the competition to win by the slimmest of margins - 0.005 seconds.\", \"from\": 326, \"to\": 515, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 330, \"end\": 332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.5780112612882662, \"rank\": 0.73003160169031, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 391, \"end\": 401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Usain_Bolt\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Usain Bolt\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Usain_Bolt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Usain_Bolt\"}, {\"begin\": 403, \"end\": 413, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carl Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\"}, {\"begin\": 418, \"end\": 429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesse_Owens\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0867415016797666e-51, \"text\": \"Jesse Owens\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesse_Owens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesse_Owens\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The photo finish was so close that the runners were forced to wait on the track and stare at the stadium's big screen to see the result.\", \"from\": 517, \"to\": 653, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After a drawn-out review, officials handed Lyles the gold medal with a time of 9.784 seconds.\", \"from\": 655, \"to\": 748, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To the roar of almost 80,000 spectators at the Stade de France, Lyles, draped in the stars and stripes, roared to cameras: \\\"America, I told you, I got next!\\\"\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 907, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 814, \"end\": 819, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.7711395273733268, \"rank\": 0.29676977195980514, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In an interview with Nine's Tony Jones, Lyles said: \\\"There was a lot of doubt, I am not going to lie.\\\"\", \"from\": 909, \"to\": 1011, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 937, \"end\": 947, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disappearance_of_Tony_Jones\", \"score\": 0.9502402002802803, \"rank\": 0.024481358432397207, \"text\": \"Tony Jones\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disappearance_of_Tony_Jones\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disappearance_of_Tony_Jones\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I thought I did not outdo Kishane there, I thought he outdid me.\", \"from\": 1013, \"to\": 1078, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When I crossed the line, I went up to him and said, 'Hey, man, I think you got that one'.\", \"from\": 1079, \"to\": 1168, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When it came out, I thought, 'Oh my gosh, I am amazing'.\\\"\", \"from\": 1170, \"to\": 1228, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 27-year-old beat out rival Jamaican Kishane Thompson (9.789) and fellow American Fred Kerley (9.81).\", \"from\": 1230, \"to\": 1334, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1261, \"end\": 1269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9924881511272834, \"rank\": 0.007568703831310905, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}, {\"begin\": 1278, \"end\": 1286, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9436701375439677, \"rank\": 0.059692322744792616, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}, {\"begin\": 1306, \"end\": 1314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997023632267799, \"rank\": 0.00026490454065167073, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The race was the first time in Olympic history all 100m runners had qualified for the final in under 10 seconds.\", \"from\": 1336, \"to\": 1448, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles' path to victory had been anything but easy as the Florida-born sprinter bypassed the traditional US college athlete route to turn professional.\", \"from\": 1450, \"to\": 1600, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1554, \"end\": 1556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.5780112612882662, \"rank\": 0.73003160169031, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The American had spent the leadup to the Olympics working on his technique and practicing his infamously poor start with coach Lance Brauman.\", \"from\": 1602, \"to\": 1743, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1606, \"end\": 1614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997023632267799, \"rank\": 0.00026490454065167073, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When the starting gun fired, his 0.178 reaction time set him off the blocks in last place as he torched his way down the straight.\", \"from\": 1745, \"to\": 1875, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His speed saved him as he gradually fought his way back among the pack by 50m and threw himself over the line to overtake Thompson by a hair's breadth.\", \"from\": 1877, \"to\": 2028, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1999, \"end\": 2007, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9436701375439677, \"rank\": 0.059692322744792616, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While Thompson actually broke the line first with his foot, it was the American whose chest first passed the finishing line - the body part which determines the victor.\", \"from\": 2030, \"to\": 2198, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2036, \"end\": 2044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9436701375439677, \"rank\": 0.059692322744792616, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}, {\"begin\": 2101, \"end\": 2109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997023632267799, \"rank\": 0.00026490454065167073, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The victory makes Lyles the first United States Olympic champion in 20 years - since Justin Gatlin won at Athens in 2004.\", \"from\": 2200, \"to\": 2321, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2218, \"end\": 2223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.7711395273733268, \"rank\": 0.29676977195980514, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 2306, \"end\": 2312, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999999622105, \"rank\": 3.77919767491799e-10, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles has set himself the goal of winning gold in the 100m, 200m and 4x100m relay after achieving the trifecta at the World Championship in Budapest.\", \"from\": 2323, \"to\": 2472, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2463, \"end\": 2471, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"score\": 0.7883714409671921, \"rank\": 0.26843762727953985, \"text\": \"Budapest\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The outspoken sprinter will now turn his focus onto the 200m sprint event which will begin on Monday before the final on Thursday (local time).\", \"from\": 2474, \"to\": 2617, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To join the conversation, pleaselog in.Do not have an account?Register  Join the conversation, you are commenting asLogout  Our Apps\", \"from\": 2619, \"to\": 2751, \"entities\": []}]}"